The '''Three Keepers''' were the guardians of the [[Three Rings]] of the [[Elves]], a term used particularly to refer to those who held the Rings at the end of the [[Third Age]], and departed over the Sea with them.<ref>{{App|B4}}, p. 1096</ref> The guardianship was unknown throughout the whole Age and it was only known later that they were held by the greatest among the [[Eldar]].<ref name=Third>{{App|TA}}, p. 1085</ref> The Three Keepers were [[Elrond]] (who received [[Vilya]]<ref name=Havens>{{RK|Havens}}, p. 1028</ref> from [[Gil-galad]]), [[Galadriel]] (who held [[Nenya]]<ref name=Havens/>) and [[Gandalf]] (who received [[Narya]]<ref>{{RK|Havens}}, p. 1030</ref> from [[Círdan]]).<ref name=Third/>

